Derangement	#61.	 complicate, involve, perplex, confound
Inattention	#458.	 put out, confuse, perplex, bewilder, moider, fluster, muddle, dazzle
Uncertainty	#475.	 put out, pose, puzzle, perplex, embarrass
Unintelligibility	#519.	 perplex &c. (bewilder). not understand &c.
Difficulty	#704.	 pose, perplex &c. (uncertain)
Painfulness	#830.	 disturb, cross, perplex, molest, tease, tire, irk, vex, mortify, wherret, worry, plague, bother, pester, bore, pother, harass, harry, badger, heckle, bait, beset, infest, persecute, importune. wring, harrow, torment, torture
